RAILS ENVIRONMENT AUTOMATIC INSTALL

This script was wrote for easily perform the setup of Rails development environment using Ubuntu Karmic Koala (9.10)

DEFAULT:

- Download, compile and install Ruby 1.8.7 Patch Level 72.
- Download, compile and install RubyGems 1.3.5
- Donwload, install and configure gemcutter
- Download, compile and install Git 1.6.5.2
- Install Apache2 http Server
- Install MySQL 5.1 Client and Server
- Install SQLite3
- Install PHP5
- Install ImageMagick
- Install Rails (latest version)

OPTIONALS:

- Set of common GEMS for Rails development
- Download and install GMate add-ons
- Install and enable Passenger for Apache2


